	ngar 30 at Magnuson Park on April 11–12\, 2026\, featuring over 100 Pacifi
	c Northwest artists selling one-of-a-kind paintings\, sculpture\, ceramics
	\, jewelry\, glass\, fiber\, and more. Enjoy live artist demonstrations\, 
	a special exhibit and youth soapstone carving sessions with the Northwest 
	Stone Sculptors Association\, local food vendors\, and a community art pro
	ject — all under one roof. Advance tickets are just $5 \\($8 at the door\\
